<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-19T00:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-19T00:29:00-05:00" n="464" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1112</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-19T00:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 19, 1917,
                                midnight</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your February 18, 7 p.m. Publication of statement has produced marked
                            impression. Cuban Secretary of State and the President have made feeling
                            response. From my viewpoint and understanding of conditions here the
                            message leaves nothing to be desired in form, spirit or principle.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>